<TEXT>
pro football veteran phil mcconkey compares 
himself to the new presidents of czechoslovakia and nicaragua in 
sizing up his chances of being elected to congress 
neither czechoslovakias vaclav havel nor nicaraguas violeta 
barrios de chamorro had prior elected experience says the gop 
candidate from new jersey 
these people have what it takes to lead their people to better 
times he says political experience has nothing to do with 
it 
mcconkey who describes himself as a skinny street kid from 
buffalo is running an outsiders race against two veteran 
republicans for the chance to face democrat marguerite chandler in 
november they are vying for the house seat being vacated by 
republican rep jim courter who is retiring 
ive got energy to burn i cant be outworked or outhustled by 
anybody mcconkey says 
mcconkey 33 began his national football league career as a 
wide receiver with the new york giants who he helped to a 1986 
super bowl victory he most recently was with the san diego 
chargers but has not signed a contract for 1990 
he models himself after housing secretary jack kemp the onetime 
buffalo bills quarterback and former new york congressman and puts 
forth a combination of energy fiscal conservatism and patriotism 
although kemp has made no endorsement in the gop primary he 
says he has offered a helping hand to encourage mcconkeys 
nonewtaxes righttolife bid 
polls show mcconkey trailing state assemblyman rodney 
frelinghuysen and state sen richard a zimmer in the gop primary 
but richard roper director of the council on new jersey affairs 
at the woodrow wilson school in princeton nj said its possible 
mcconkey could win if the other two candidates split the moderate 
gop vote 
rutgers university political scientist steve salmore was more 
pessimistic about mcconkeys chances noting that few issues 
distinguish the three candidates other than abortion where 
frelinghuysen and zimmer are prochoice 
mcconkey however is his own cheering squad 
im always the underdog and up against insurmountable odds 
he said as an example of his determination mcconkey cites his 
decision to return to football at age 27 after five years as a navy 
helicopter pilot 
mcconkey a 1979 graduate of the naval academy proceeds 
undaunted against frelinghuysen whose father once held courters 
house seat and zimmer whose state legislative district dominates 
the congressional district 
pressure is landing a 10ton helicopter on the back of a 
rolling pitching deck at night or standing under a punt in front 
of 80000 people in the stands and millions on tv with 11 maniacs 
foaming at the mouth ready to decapitate you he said 
mcconkey who has put 40000 of his own money into the 
campaign has postponed his planned june wedding and is focusing 
solely on the upcoming primary 
my life goes from here to june 5 if you start worrying about 
things that arent in line with your goal its taking away from 
your energy and enthusiasm he said 
mcconkey talks about attracting minorities to the party 
although roper describes the congressional districts voters as 
overwhelmingly white moderate to middleincome republicans 
its an issue of bringing the party back to a lincoln party a 
party of the people mcconkey said he echoes the politics of 
inclusion philosophy of kemp and former new jersey gop gov 
thomas h kean 
mcconkey wont discuss plans for his pro football career except 
to say retirement from the chargers has been on his mind 
football is an avocation not a vocation he said 
his campaign has relied heavily on radio and cable television 
advertising as well as oldfashioned community campaign 
appearances he also involves sports colleagues including former 
nfl teammates lawrence taylor phil simms and mark bavaro 
