<TEXT>
less than three years ago boris n yeltsin was 
reviled in the soviet press attacked by top party officials and 
rebuffed by his former mentor soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev 
somehow he turned it all to his advantage 
yeltsin a burly 59yearold siberian won election today to a 
powerful and visible post the presidency of the russian 
federation by far the soviet unions largest republic 
it wasnt a quick and easy victory it took three strenuous 
rounds of balloting in the russian congress gorbachev opposed 
yeltsins candidacy 
but once again yeltsin showed his talent for overcoming odds 
for seizing the moment for using popular support to get what he 
wants 
and as usual if powerful higherups stood in his way it only 
seemed to strengthen him and his populist message of radical 
economic and political reforms and less power for the central 
government 
in 1985 yeltsin a construction engineer by trade was an 
obscure official in the ural mountains industrial city of 
sverdlovsk not far from his native village of butka 
then gorbachev brought him to moscow to take over the capital 
citys communist party organization and gave him a nonvoting seat 
on the ruling communist party politburo 
it didnt take yeltsin long to start making waves 
he showed little reverence for the party hierarchy he 
campaigned in stores and on trolley buses to improve food supplies 
and public services he spoke out against special privileges for 
the government and party elite 
the gravellyvoiced whitehaired yeltsin quickly won a 
following 
people identify with yeltsin the weekly moscow news wrote 
last year in a fullpage story headlined the boris yelsin 
phenomenon 
muscovites were tired of watching their leaders rocket by in 
sleek limousines while they stood in line to buy soap sugar and 
other scarce items yeltsins borshchtineverypot message had 
immediate appeal 
like millions of other soviet citizens yeltsin became 
increasingly impatient with the pace of gorbachevs reforms 
characteristically he did not hesitate to say so and 
characteristically he went too far 
in 1987 he made a stinging speech to a closed meeting of the 
communist party central committee criticizing the slow pace of 
reforms 
that earned him a sharp reprimand from his former mentor 
gorbachev and brought vitriolic attacks from the party officials 
who accused him of dealing a stab in the back to economic 
reform 
the criticism of yeltsin was published in the press he was 
stripped of his post as moscow party chief and hospitalized for 
heart trouble the word went out that he was finished politically 
gorbachev and yeltsin never did patch things up and yeltsin 
remained on the outs with top leaders 
but he made that rift work for him the open disdain of the 
communist party apparatus enhanced yeltsins populist image and 
helped him win the backing of millions of supporters 
gorbachev actively campaigned against yeltsins bid for the 
russian presidency he told the russian congress last week that 
yeltsins call for russian sovereignty was an attempt to cut 
russia off from socialism 
yeltsin in turn spoke against the soviet governments program 
for gradually transforming the countrys crippled centrally planned 
economy to a partial market economy 
that program which will eventually double the cost of food 
caused panicbuying in moscow some congressional deputies said 
yeltsins candidacy got a boost from public anxiety over the plan 
although yeltsins win today seemed like a sudden triumph his 
comeback didnt happen all at once 
after his fall from political grace in 1987 he began rebuilding 
his power base that led to a landslide victory in march 1989 in 
direct popular elections to the soviet congress of peoples 
deputies the national parliament 
yeltsin was swept into office with almost 90 percent of the 
vote crushing his apparatusbacked opponent 
later that year he carried out a deft procedural maneuver to 
win election to the supreme soviet the national legislature 
and early this year he was elected a deputy of the russian 
federation congress which today chose him president he also 
remains a member of the partys policymaking central committee 
now his image as a man who can take on the system and win is 
stronger than ever 
