children witnesses said they saw them driven in away in military 
vehicles 
the fighting began last week with the death of an opposition 
leader and oil companies drastically cut production gabon earns 
80 percent of its income from oil and would quickly run out of 
money without it 
president omar bongos government imposed a state of siege 
monday night throughout port gentils province and sent troops in 
today to restore order 
in paris today the stateowned oil company elfaquitaine 
announced it would gradually resume production on its 60 offshore 
rigs production was expected to reach half of the 101000 barrels 
normally produced per day and climb to 80 percent wednesday a 
company spokesman said 
