dimitri de grunwald who produced the film the 
millionairess with peter sellers and sophia loren has died at 
age 76 a family death notice said tuesday 
de grunwald died saturday at his home in hove on the english 
south coast 
he was the son of a czarist diplomat and was born in st 
petersburg now leningrad in 1914 his family brought him to 
england when they escaped during the revolution 
de grunwald started his career in a chemical company then moved 
to advertising and became a movie producer on his own account after 
collaborating with his brother anatole in making films including 
the way to the stars the winslow boy and the 
demiparadise 
after the millionairess in 1960 in which sellers played an 
indian doctor de grunwald produced shalako with sean connery 
and brigitte bardot murphys war with peter otoole and other 
movies 
he started a new career in 1980 as a consultant to a 
pharmaceutical company 
de grunwald is survived by his wife vera and a son his 
brother died in 1967 
