<TEXT>
tortoises tend to move rather slowly 
but the brookfield zoos was so slow on its annual trek to its 
summer quarters that its keepers had to call a cab 
the 450pound tortoise named peter has taken the quartermile 
walk from the reptile house to an outdoor yard every memorial day 
for at least 17 years 
peter and its keepers set out monday at about 1030 am 
but by 1245 pm peter had covered only about 30 yards said 
zoo spokeswoman hannah jennings 
some plants distracted him and he stopped to eat them 
at 115 pm the keepers gave up loaded peter onto a truck and 
hauled him the rest of the way 
the tortoise from aldabra island in the indian ocean was 
brought to the zoo as an adult and is estimated to be 40 to 60 
years old said joyce peterson senior keeper at the reptile house 
