an agreement to expand and possibly 
quadruple commercial air travel between the united states and the 
soviet union is ready for signing at the summit while negotiators 
are still working on deeper cuts in nuclear weapons 
the agreement concluded on sunday will expand the travel route 
to involve more carriers and cities and inaugurate regular cargo 
flights between the two countries it represents closer ties 
between the superpowers as soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
