the 54 ruling in a case from new york extends socalled double 
jeopardy protection against multiple prosecutions for some criminal 
defendants the court said someone convicted of a relatively minor 
offense generally may not be retried on more serious charges based 
on the same alleged conduct 
the case is grady vs corbin 89474 
 
ku klux klan 
 
the court rejected an appeal by two ku klux klan groups and four 
men ordered to pay more than 800000 for organizing a 
demonstration that turned into a violent attack on civil rights 
marchers in georgia 
the court without comment let stand a ruling that the 
punitivedamages award did not violate the freespeech rights of 
the kkk and its sympathizers 
the case is stephens vs mckinney 891558 
 
bail 
 
the court increased the federal governments power to keep some 
criminal defendants behind bars while they await trial even if a 
key bail law was violated 
the justices by a 63 vote spared the government from having 
to free on bail some defendants deemed to be dangerous or a risk to 
flee before trial 
the case is us vs montalvomurillo 89163 
 
child abuse 
 
the court refused to revive a lawsuit in behalf of a child 
abused after illinois officials placed her isn the home of her aunt 
and uncle 
the court without comment turned away arguments that public 
officials should not be shielded from federal suits when they 
knowingly expose children to abuse in foster homes 
the case is doe vs bobbitt 891218 
 
tax debts 
 
the court made it more difficult for the federal government to 
collect all taxes owed by bankrupt corporations 
by an 81 vote the court thwarted the governments attempt to 
hold officials of bankrupt corporations personally responsible for 
paying the owed taxes 
the case is us vs energy resources co 89255 
 
overseas banks 
 
the court in a case with potentially billions of dollars at 
stake ordered further hearings to decide whether us banks with 
branch offices overseas must pay depositors after foreign 
governments freeze those accounts 
the court by an 81 vote set aside a ruling that required 
citibank to pay a depositor whose account was frozen by the 
philippine government of ferdinand marcos 
the case is citibank vs wells fargo 881260 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

