the presidents of iran and iraq may hold 
their first direct meeting in the next few weeks for peace talks to 
formally end the iraniraq war a senior plo official said tuesday 
if the talks take place they would be the first direct 
negotiations between the countries since 1988 when a 
unsponsored ceasefire halted eight years of fighting 
peace negotiations began five days after the truce took effect 
in august 1988 but they quickly deadlocked 
arab officials in baghdad said they believe the threat from 
israel perceived by arab leaders is acting as a catalyst to push 
the foes toward a peace treaty 
