block in earlier peace talks but according to press reports in 
tehran and kuwait saddam has now conceded that sovereignty over 
the shattalarab is negotiable 
both leaders are under pressure to formally end their war 
iran needs stability to carry out reconstruction and revitalize 
its economy since ayatollah ruhollah khomeini died last june 
tehran has quietly dropped its demands for huge war reparations and 
for an iraqi admission it started the war 
iraq meanwhile needs to reopen its major port at basra on the 
shattalarab which has been closed since the war began it also 
is under domestic pressure to get back its 50000 prisoners of war 
