<TEXT>
boris n yeltsin has embarrassed president mikhail 
s gorbachev again by transforming popular support into a political 
office despite a highlevel campaign against him 
the prize this time was the presidency of the soviet unions 
largest republic the russian federation 
yeltsins victory tuesday in the republics congress of peoples 
deputies presents a formidable political challenge for gorbachev 
who invested his own political clout last week in a rare public 
browbeating of yeltsin 
the 59yearold yeltsin confronted gorbachevs program of 
moderate reforms with a sweeping call for a more radical steps 
including devolution of political and economic decisionmaking from 
central to local authorities 
gorbachev told the russian parliament last week that yeltsins 
call for russian sovereignty was an attempt to cut russia off 
from socialism 
those words may have slowed the rise of yeltsin who passed the 
531vote majority he needed only after three ballots but they did 
not prevent his ascendancy into a leadership position from which 
gorbachev cannot fire him 
gorbachev who retains the top kremlin jobs of soviet president 
and general secretary of the soviet communist party left moscow on 
tuesday for canada and the united states where he is to meet 
president bush on wednesday 
yeltsins victory stood in contrast to gorbachevs foreign trip 
a showcase of the soviet leaders foreign policy success at a time 
of sagging popularity at home 
his election also coincided with a nationwide wave of panic 
buying triggered by the governments plan to raise prices in a 
transition to a partial market economy 
yeltsin was born feb 1 1931 in the village of butka in the 
sverdlovsk region of the urals he was educated as a construction 
engineer for several years he worked in building organizations in 
sverdlovsk in 19761985 he was head of the sverdlovsk regional 
party committee 
shortly after gorbachev came to power in 1985 he summoned 
yeltsin from sverdlovsk to take over the communist party 
organization in moscow gorbachev also gave yeltsin a nonvoting 
seat on the ruling communist party politburo 
yeltsins populist style soon won him the affection of 
muscovites 
he chopped the capitals party apparatus campaigned in stores 
on trolley buses and on television to improve food supplies and 
public services and spoke out against special privileges for the 
government and party elite 
for many muscovites who watch their leaders rocket by in sleek 
limousines while they stand in line to buy soap and other scarce 
items yeltsins borschtineverypot message has immediate appeal 
yeltsin along with millions of soviets became increasingly 
impatient with gorbachevs perestroika or economic reform 
program he called for faster changes and became an outspoken 
public figure 
then he went too far in a speech to a closed meeting of the 
communist party central committee in 1987 yeltsin criticized the 
slow pace of gorbachevs reforms he also lashed out at 
conservative forces led by politburo member yegor k ligachev 
that speech brought yeltsin a scathing reprimand from gorbachev 
and vitriolic attacks from other party officials who accused him 
of dealing a stab in the back to economic reform 
the criticism of yeltsin was published in the press he was 
stripped of his post as moscow party chief then hospitalized for 
heart trouble 
the word went out that the siberian politician was broken in 
his own biography published this year yeltsin said he felt 
demoralized and beaten but not defeated 
now after two years adversity and the open opposition of the 
communist party apparatus has only swelled yeltsins reputation 
millions of supporters relish his open battles with party leaders 
and cheer his calls to ease the brutal grind of soviet daily life 
he carries a simple message in simple style using his throaty 
bass to boom out accusations and demands in simple phrases his 
square doughy face set in a characteristic snarl his strapping 
erect figure topped by a smooth sweep of silver hair 
people identify with yeltsin the weekly moscow news wrote 
last year in a fullpage story headlined the boris yelsin 
phenomenon 
hes a victim of dislike on the part of higherups who of us 
hasnt been in the same position the weekly said and he is 
being slighted for refusing to seek their approval who hasnt 
dreamed of doing that 
the first big step in his political comeback was a landslide 
victory in march 1989 in direct popular elections to the soviet 
congress of peoples deputies the national parliament yeltsin was 
swept into office with almost 90 percent of the vote obtaining 
approval from more than 5 million muscovites and crushing his 
apparatusbacked opponent 
later that year he carried out a deft procedural maneuver to 
win election to the supreme soviet the national legislature and 
early this year he was elected a deputy of the rssian federation 
congress which tuesday chose him president 
he still is a member of the partys policymaking central 
committee 
