a former vietnam war hero an exambassador 
and a movie stuntman were among house candidates whose financial 
disclosure forms were released tuesday 
the disclosures of income holdings and liabilities are required 
of challengers as well as for incumbents holdings and liabilities 
are listed in low and high ranges rather than in exact amounts 
randall h cunningham an exfighter pilot who was a vietnam 
ace and an instructor in the navys elite top gun school 
is a republican running for the seat held by rep jim bates 
dcalif 
cunningham listed 77666 in income for 1989 while his holdings 
ranged from a low of 465008 to more than 820000 he had no 
liabilities 
another republican vying for the seat is joseph a ghougassian 
who was the us ambassador to the persian gulf nation of qatar 
from 1985 to 1989 
his entire salary in 1989 was from the state department 
totaling 46502 he listed unearned income ranging from 30005 to 
90000 
ghougassians holdings however were extensive ranging from 
680006 to more than 13 million he also listed 100000 to 
250000 in liabilities 
bates who is running for reelection came under fire last 
october from the house ethics committee which found that he had 
violated a house rule prohibiting sexual harassment and an ethics 
guideline barring campaign work in a congressional office former 
female staffers of bates had complained about his behavior 
james h dingeman jr a parttime stunt driver for television 
ads and for movies is a republican challenging rep david bonior 
dmich his partys chief deputy whip 
dingeman who also is an environmental consultant listed 1989 
income of 670781 which included the sale of a his interest in a 
steel company he also listed unearned income ranging from 21008 
to 72500 and holdings from 40009 to 155000 he had no 
liabilities 
walter dudycz a republican state senator and chicago police 
detective on leave is challenging 13term chicago democrat frank 
annunzio dudycz listed a 1989 income of 59660 dudycz had no 
unearned income no holdings and no liabilities last year 
three democrats are running to unseat house republican whip newt 
gingrich of georgia 
david worley who lost to gingrich two years ago did not list 
any 1989 salary or liabilities and his only holding was an 
individual retirement account worth 1 to 1000 
roger b marietta mayor of fayetteville listed 51752 in 
earned income last year and an additional 2 to 2000 in unearned 
income his holdings were 5000 or less liabilities were listed 
from 5001 to 15000 
joe forrest a former eastern air lines pilot earned 33002 
last year including 16800 in strike benefits during the pilots 
walkout against the airline his unearned income was 6007 to 
22500 and his holdings ranged from 5001 and 15000 he had no 
liabilities 
last march the house ethics committee ordered gingrich to amend 
his financial disclosure forms to reflect participation in the 
purchase along with his daughter of her home in georgia four 
years ago 
the committee also criticized two letters sent on his letterhead 
in 1986 and 1987 promoting a forprofit senior citizens cruise 
however the committee also decided not to pursue a formal 
investigation of gingrichs financial dealings as had been 
requested by rep bill alexander dark 
c 
