police and farmers said they fear osmarino amancio now in 
hiding faces assassinated by landowners who oppose his 
environmentalist policies 
there have been five attempts on amancios life this year 
the former head of the rubber tappers union chico mendes was 
shot and killed on dec 22 1988 outside his home in the amazon 
town of xapuri near the bolivian border 
in brazil mendes is revered as a man who died protecting the 
rights of peasants against powerful ranchers who often hire gunmen 
to do their bidding in the jungle us producers are planning a 
movie based on mendes life 
landowners have cleared huge tracts of amazon forest to provide 
grazing land for their cattle cleared jungle land is initially 
fertile but quickly loses its nutrients 
poor peasants and rubber tappers who make their living 
collecting rubber from the trees oppose destruction of the forest 
amancio is one of the leading activists of the rubber tappers 
union the union is led by julio barbosa who took over after 
mendes assassination 
mendes was the most prominent of almost 1000 people most of 
them peasant farmers killed at the order of large landowners the 
past decade according to amnesty international only two of the 
gunmen responsible for the crimes have been punished 
osmarino has suffered a number of death threats and police 
will now accompany him and also be posted at his home joao 
martins a federal police spokesman in brasilia said tuesday he 
said police were acting at the request of justice minister bernardo 
cabral 
rosa a director of the national council of rubber tappers in 
rio branco 2600 miles northwest of rio said the protection is 
welcome but it is not enough landowners have gunmen who circulate 
freely in the region and they must be locked up 
rosa who refused to be further identified said amancio may 
still refuse to emerge even with police protection 
the police were guarding chico mendes and that didnt prevent 
his death she said 
amancio 33 was based in the small town of brasilea 93 miles 
southwest of rio branco on bolivias border 
if the government doesnt take serious action there will be a 
bloodbath rosa said 
in a recent interview amancio vowed to continue his fight to 
protect the amazon despite the threats on his life 
i know my life is in danger he said but if we want to 
