<TEXT>
harvard university president derek c 
bok announced his resignation tuesday after presiding over two 
turbulent decades of sweeping changes at the nations oldest and 
richest university 
it is time for me to step down and allow a new president to 
provide fresh energy and continuity of leadership through the next 
decade bok said in a statement 
bok 60 became the universitys 25th president in 1971 he said 
he will step down at the end of the next school year and had no 
immediate longterm plans 
theres no perfect time to leave a job like this which ive 
loved bok said at the end of a hectic day after the 
announcement but ive felt 20 years was the outside limit i 
thought of leaving around the 350th anniversary of harvard but 
the harvard corporation asked me to stay on for a couple of years 
its time for me to look for a new challenge 
his presidency began amid student demonstrations against the 
vietnam war it comes to a close as women and minorities argue for 
greater representation at the school most recently a black law 
professor drew publicity by taking an unpaid leave to pressure the 
law school into giving tenure to a woman from a minority group 
in recent years bok also was the target of protesters seeking 
total divestment of university stock holdings in companies doing 
business in south africa and by clerical staff who formed a union 
after a 13year fight 
through it all the school has expanded in all directions 
a core curriculum of basic studies was instituted women gained 
equal access to the previously allmale college and the school 
became more accessible to parttime students by expanding the 
extension and summer schools 
also under his direction the john f kennedy school of 
government was developed into a major professional school two art 
museums were added and athletic facilities were expanded 
gifts to the university rose from 50 million at the start of 
his presidency to more than 200 million this year a new 
investment organization harvard management co was created to 
manage the universitys endowment and the endowment rose from 1 
billion in 1971 to approximately 5 billion the nations richest 
most of boks efforts at the 17500student school were lowkey 
he worked behind the scenes to maintain traditions at harvard 
which celebrated its 350th anniversary in 1986 
but he was a ready defender of ideals 
when thenus education secretary william bennett blasted 
harvards core curriculum of required courses such as moral 
reasoning as not rigorous enough bok shot back 
instead of pursuing these questions in an informed and sober 
manner bennett has followed his penchant for delivering highly 
publicized polemics against educational practices which he has not 
studied in detail said bok 
bok spoke out in 1982 about professors pursuing commercial 
profit in biogenetic research risking a loss of academic integrity 
bok often ranked among americas most influential educators 
drew wide praise as word of his resignation spread 
hes absolutely one of the leading presidents not simply 
because its harvard but he has provided outstanding leadership 
said robert hochstein of the carnegie foundation for the 
advancement of teaching 
the university said a committee was being formed to find a 
successor for bok who had been the subject of wide speculation 
that he would step down 
bok a stanford university graduate earned a law degree from 
harvard in 1954 he joined the harvard law school faculty in 1958 
and became dean of that school in 1968 
he is the author of several books including one on labor law 
with watergate prosecutor archibald cox and three on higher 
education 
he has served as chairman of the american council on education 
and the association of american universities and as a member of the 
board of the national association of independent colleges and 
universities 
