<TEXT>
the scrantonian tribune a 134yearold 
morning newspaper published its last edition may 21 
its name and some assets were purchased by the scranton times 
which said it would rename its morning paper the tribune and 
distribute it to subscrirtising is 
strong enough to proceed but they have delayed its reappearance 
until late july 
the 17yearold feminist magazine suspended publication in 
december because of heavy losses and a sharp decline in advertising 
in march plans were announced to resume publication without ads 
starting in june but andrea kaplan a spokeswoman for the 
