breakdown wesker says 
a second radio play yardsale was later performed as part 
of a double bill on stage 
wesker says he would write more if the money were better even 
the most successful radio dramas pay a fraction of the 35000 to 
50000 or more that a hit play can generate for its writer 
david zane mairowitz an american writer based in france says 
hes one of the few people in the world who can live off radio 
drama his plays are produced first in britain then translated and 
sold on the continent 
