<TEXT>
 
triumph of the spirit rcacolumbia home video vhsbeta 
8995 rated r 
 
triumph of the spirit is as subtle as a right to the jaw 
and at times just as powerful 
at other times it swings and misses 
a holocaust film that came out late last year triumph of the 
spirit was nearly forgotten thanks to the nearsimultaneous 
releases of the acclaimed enemies a love story and the 
costagavras drama music box 
but triumph couldnt be more different while those films 
are about memory with the holocaust a nightmare lurking 
offscreen triumph shot on location in auschwitz dares to 
show the unshowable 
the film is based on the true story of salamo arouch the 
middleweight boxing champion of the balkan countries in 1938 after 
the nazis occupied greece he and his family and friends were 
deported to auschwitz arouch used by the nazis to box with other 
prisoners survived and now lives in israel with his wife children 
and grandchildren 
triumph is relentless deliberately hard to take with no 
time for the soulsearching of enemies or music box 
they promised us a new life in poland arouch willem dafoe 
recalls as he speaks nazis are squeezing greek jews into cattle 
cars and shipping them off to their new life in auschwitz 
blows big and small rain down the nazis take their valuables 
shave their heads and make men and women wear the same drab 
uniforms prisoners are kicked literally out of bed each morning 
and drag themselves back at night beaten down by a day of marching 
and lifting 
screaming matches break out over a pair of shoes a woman breaks 
down and cries as she begs her friend for a few drops of broth 
when arouch steals a moment with his girlfriend allegra wendy 
gazelle he embraces her as if he were a starving man sniffing a 
loaf of warm bread 
the final solution is never far away gas chambers hangings 
commanders coolly selecting the next round of victims 
arouch however is spared he kos a guard who pushed him down 
a hill and becomes a valuable commodity to the commanding officers 
who bet on him in boxing matches with other prisoners arouch wins 
every fight 
so triumph becomes a story of triumphs physical moral 
and spiritual arouch is bloodied but not defeated 
all i have left is my love for allegra he says after the 
camp has been liberated and his family killed shoulders slumped 
arouch exits down a long and empty road walking gingerly under an 
endless gray sky 
if this video comes up short dont blame dafoe excellent as a 
man who learns to duck punches in and out of the ring costars 
robert loggia as arouchs ailing father and edward james olmos 
the camp gypsy are both solid 
but dafoe has to keep a straight face with such lines as you 
still taste like apricots and how can we do this to our 
brothers 
the direction by robert young dominick and eugene is 
unimaginative and worse the music soars and swells like the 
soundtrack of an old bette davis movie a symphony seeming to rise 
with every tear that falls 
how many rounds arouch asks when offered the chance to 
fight 
rounds the commander responds no rounds you fight until 
one cant get up 
triumph of the spirit lasts a full 15 give it a split 
decision 
</TEXT>
