the museum of fine arts in houston has opened its gallery of far 
eastern art after a closing of more than two years because of space 
limitations 
the gallery which opened on may 12 includes more than 60 
paintings sculptures and ceramics from japan china and india 
recent acquisitions are a 6th century japanese haniwa warrior of 
terracotta and a pair of japanese sixpanel screens illustrating 
the tale of genji from the late 17th and early 18th century 
elsewhere the luman reed gallery will open at the new york 
historical society in new york city presenting the 18th and 19th 
century art patrons entire collection of american and european 
paintings for the first time in more than 100 years 
the gallery will open on nov 13 
