<TEXT>
after 35 years bo diddley wants his payday 
its nice to be called a legend it was fun playing the white 
house induction into the rock and roll hall of fame was 
flattering and telling center fielder bo jackson that he didnt 
know diddley was a laugh 
but now bo wants more bo wants cash 
i feel like america owes me something more than just saying 
oh the great bo diddley the 61yearold artist said in a 
recent interview 
elvis presley copied me and i used to wouldnt say anything 
about it when they found the white boy who could do what i was 
doing then they shoved me back in the corner and he went on to las 
vegas where all the money was but bo diddley never got a chance 
to get involved he says 
i have no bitterness against elvis or any other white 
entertainer that records black music but i think there should be 
some recognition as to where he got the stuff from dont come up 
and steal my stuff and say you wrote it because thats a lie 
its not just elvis who rode the bo diddley beat to success the 
trademark guitar sound that hes played during six decades anchors 
the whos magic bus bruce springsteens shes the one 
buddy hollys not fade away johnny otis willie and the hand 
jive elvis costellos lovers walk and george michaels 
faith 
diddley like other rhythm and blues artists in the late 1940s 
and 50s was paid a flat fee for his recordings and received no 
royalty payments on record sales but over the years hes found 
his music on records around the world in places i aint never 
heard of in my life 
but wheres the money he says the thing that hurts me so 
bad is that every time i come up with something it looks like 
somebody jumped on it they make money with it and i cant get 
arrested with it 
everybody says oh youve got such a negative attitude 
guys can always tell bo you shouldnt be hollering about that 
thats water under the bridge yes its water under the bridge 
but my kids were deprived of a lot of things because the water went 
under the bridge and im not at all happy about that 
diddley has been entertaining almost from the day he was born 
otha ellis bates on dec 30 1928 in mccomb miss he was later 
adopted by his mothers cousin and took on the name ellis mcdaniel 
which his wife calls him to this day 
when he was 5 the family moved to chicago where he learned the 
violin at the ebenezer baptist church he learned the guitar at age 
10 he entertained passersby on street corners taking inspiration 
from the rhythm and blues bands playing in local clubs 
in his early teens he played on chicagos maxwell street and 
acquired his stage name a moniker derived from a bo diddley 
a onestringed guitar for four years beginning in 1951 he played 
at the 708 club on the south side 
in july 1955 he was signed to the checker record label and his 
first single bo diddley was a success he appeared on the 
ed sullivan show shortly thereafter radio disc jockey alan 
freed called his music rock n roll 
i was first to be called rock n roll not little richard 
not elvis presley not buddy holly none of them i was the first 
one diddley says 
he stood out on stage with his homemade square guitar 
darkrimmed glasses black leather jacket and black hat with a 
diamondshaped turquoise pinned to the front 
im an entertainer im a showman im not a guitarist says 
diddley when youre dealing with cats like myself youre dealing 
with a real entertainer a person who knows what the stage is built 
for 
its not the same at home where hes ellis to his wife and bo 
pop to his grandchildren hes also no rebel off stage serving a 
stint in the 1970s as a sheriff in new mexico he considers himself 
patriotic 
im here baby im a piece of this dirt or whatever it is i 
didnt come from no africa he says 
sometimes he can be found building a porch in deboe fla for 
his 70by 24foot trailer home surrounded by rose bushes fruit 
trees and grass 
he says the home is so big it makes him feel like nobility 
but he knows what it can connote to some people 
its comfortable it doesnt bother me what people think 
because theres so many people that live in those trailers that got 
more money than bo diddley i am a regular person he says 
he is still paying for a large home in hawthorne fla which he 
moved away from when a previous marriage ended someone he says 
should do a benefit for bo diddley to clear him of his 300000 
debt 
at 55 i couldnt retire i couldnt even think about it he 
says 
meanwhile hell keep touring the country playing here and 
there and mostly near his home in the same sort of venues where 
hes been displaying his act for parts of five decades 
with all his business failings one of diddleys greatest 
achievements came last year when he was in the nike sneaker 
commercial 
the nike commercial did more for me than anything done for me 
in the last 20 years everybody knows bo diddley now just because 
i said you dont know diddley thats all i said i aint done 
nothing else i dont understand this part of it 
</TEXT>
