<TEXT>
the tall stranger rode into town and 
stayed because he found whats left of the code of the west was 
still alive in las cruces 
he packed no gun he had a typewriter 
a recent stanford university graduate school alumnus in 1966 
mark medoff drove into las cruces in a black 62 volkswagen beetle 
with no idea that he would become one of americas premier 
playwrights 
floridaborn medoff just turned 50 is a westerner now he 
teaches screenwriting playwriting acting and directing at new 
mexico state university and writes on his computer in the 
woodpaneled library of his spanish colonial home 
the author of the tonywinning children of a lesser god and 
obiewinning when you comin back red ryder says many of his 
plays are about old west values and the fall of the hero as medoff 
recalls from growing up in miami beach 
i think we dont have heroes in this country particularly 
anymore medoff said during an interview at his home we have 
demystified all our heroes we dont have people we look up to 
hes not particularly optimistic about what has replaced them 
his new play stumps is the second sequel to red ryder 
in it vietnam amputee stephen ryder and a wheelchairridden 
comrade try to sell a screenplay to a pornography producer a 
sociopath in clergymans clothing who brutalizes them and ryders 
vietnamese wife lin 
after two new mexico productions stumps is ready for larger 
venues and medoff has started sending it out 
the challenge of stumps was to create an educated 
articulate character without a conscience the rev calvin rhodes 
whod be seen as human not allegorical 
i guess my greatest fear about calvin rhodes is that hes not 
simply an aberration but that hes a kind of character we may see 
proliferate around us in our lives medoff says 
ryders luck has been lousy with sociopaths in when you 
comin back red ryder a gunman holds patrons of a desert diner 
hostage and wounds one the plays roots were westerns 
the bad guys ride into town they go into the saloon and they 
start tormenting the guy who drinks milk he says 
in the first sequel the heart outright we learn the gunman 
later was killed by state police 
but the author has met such bad guys only in his head ive 
always maintained that i have all the worst of my worst characters 
in me and i think we all do 
he recalls a happy childhood listening to the real red ryder on 
the radio along with the lone ranger and straight arrow 
my fathers a doctor my mothers a psychologist my father 
was a superb pianist my mothers a very fine painter the house 
was always full of music and art and books and it was a very nice 
upbringing a very civilized congenial upbringing and yet i 
think that in a way we in my generation all bridled against our 
very civility 
the wild one with marlon brando impressed him as a 
teenager in that film biker brando halfterrorizes 
halfmesmerizes a smalltown diner 
i was about 15 and looking at my uppermiddleclass jewish 
welleducated self thinking god i wish i had the guts and 
the wherewithal to put on black leather and get on a hog and go out 
and make trouble 
instead the 6foottall medoff channeled his aggressions into 
sports tore up a knee and had to quit football he now has a 
passion for golf 
he was also 15 when he started writing prose with support from 
his parents but with their warning about the vagaries of literary 
life he studied creative writing at the university of miami one 
of his stories was published by random house in prize college 
stories of 1963 he got his masters degree at stanford and 
accepted a position at first reluctantly at new mexico state 
it worried him that it was an agricultural school with cows 
right on campus but he soon found it a more diverse barnyard 
the first people he met were involved in the las cruces community 
theater 
one was actor bill frankfather who suggested medoff write a play 
and theyd put it on so i did and they did and that was the 
beginning 
frankfather played rhodes in the new mexico repertory theatre 
production of stumps this winter in santa fe and albuquerque 
the nurturing and support from campus and community and the 
spirit of the old west keep medoff in new mexico he likes his 
plays to succeed in new york but he prefers to stay here 
i have an affinity for the old west and i think theres still 
a residual civility here theres just something about the 
warmth of the people 
he met his wife stephanie in one of his literature courses 
they have three children debra 22 rachel 15 and jessica 11 
parenthood changed medoff as a writer 
the world is so much with us and the world is so full of 
violence and seems to be so much fuller today than it was yesterday 
of a lack of conscience that for my children i know im trying to 
write material that brings people face to face with that lack of 
conscience in hopes of fostering change he said 
when a brother of one of medoffs students was murdered several 
years ago medoff created the homage that follows which was to 
have been his statement on sociopaths 
but he became sympathetic to the killer even though what he 
did was unforgivable it became clear he was not without 
conscience 
so stumps was summoned up from the depths of his anger 
</TEXT>
