<TEXT>
inflation in the 12nation european community 
jumped 09 percent during april boosted by sharply higher consumer 
prices in britain portugal and greece the ecs statistical agency 
eurostat reported tuesday 
the increase was faster than a 05 percent rise in march and up 
from a 08 percent increase a year earlier 
eurostat said the consumer price index for the ec as a whole 
rose 54 percent in the 12 months to april higher than a 47 
percent increase in the united states and a 24 percent rise in 
japan during the same period 
eurostat said a 30 percent surge in britain accounted for a 
large part of the ecwide increase 
britains april figure was pushed up by the introduction of the 
community charge on adults or socalled poll tax rises in excise 
duties on alcohol tobacco and gasoline as well as increases in 
public utilities rents and in seasonal food costs 
the 3 percent april increase in britain was the highest since 
april 1980 when the consumer price index rose 34 percent 
eurostat said 
eurostat said a 17 percent jump in greece and a 12 percent 
increase in portugal also drove up the inflation rate for the 
community as a whole 
in the year to april greece had the highest ec inflation at 
179 percent portugal had price increases of 129 percent britain 
94 percent spain 70 percent italy 62 percent ireland 42 
percent luxembourg 36 percent belgium and france 32 percent 
denmark 24 percent west germany 23 percent and the netherlands 
21 percent 
</TEXT>
