<TEXT>
cadbury schweppes plc the british beverages and 
sweets manufacturer agreed tuesday to buy most of the noncola 
soft drinks business of source perrier of france for 125 million 
pounds or 211 million 
the purchase includes the noncarbonated fruit drinks oasis and 
bali the fruit drink concentrate atoll and the bottling rights for 
gini a carbonated lemon drink cadbury schweppes said 
cadbury schweppes said 1989 sales of the businesses being 
acquired was 913 million pounds or 154 million 
the acquisition includes two manufacturing plants near paris and 
one in marseilles cadbury schweppes said the company is not 
buying a couple other brands and perriers bottling rights to 
pepsicola products 
the deal is conditional on clearance by the french authorities 
cadbury schweppes said the acquisition is being made by the 
purchase of shares in compagnie dexploitation de boissons 
refraichissantes a wholly owned subsidiary of source perrier 
perrier executives have said that the company wants to 
concentrate on its flagship bottled water interests because it 
expects that market to expand dramatically in coming years 
earlier this year perrier withdrew its mineral water from 
shelves worldwide after some samples of the water were discovered 
to contain traces of benzene a naturally occurring chemical said 
to be cancer inducing 
source perrier since has reintroduced the mineral water after 
carrying out checks and repairs to prevent benzene from entering 
the finished product 
