<DOCNO> AP900529-0230 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
officials from 40 nations on tuesday signed a 
treaty creating a 12 billion development bank to finance eastern 
europes conversion to a market economy 
the european bank for reconstruction and development will be a 
catalyst between the capital and knowhow of the west and the 
businesses of the east french president francois mitterrand said 
at a signing ceremony 
mitterand proposed creating the bank last november as communist 
regimes crumbled across eastern europe he said the 42 founding 
nations would not reduce their individual support to third world 
countries 
the bank is expected to become operation in april 1991 the 12 
european community nations hold a controlling 51 percent interest 
in the bank although the united states is the single biggest 
shareholder with 10 percent interest 
eastern european countries will hold 135 percent interest 
under the banks statutes twothirds of the founding members 
must ratify the treaty before the bank can start lending money to 
countries in eastern europe that have embraced democratic 
principles 
the bank will allocate at least 60 percent of its loans to the 
private sector in eastern europe and the rest to public projects 
the fivemonth negotiations to create the bank were punctuated 
by disputes over the soviet unions membership and the choices for 
a venue and president 
early in the talks the united states raised objections to 
accepting the soviet union as a full member the dispute was 
resolved by allowing the soviets to join but limiting borrowing 
for three years to the amount of capital they contribute 
the netherlands led a rebellion by six other small western 
european countries against plans to locate the banks headquarters 
in london under the presidency of jacques attali of france one of 
mitterrands top aides 
dutch officials saying the big european powers were too 
dominant in multinational instituions lobbied in vain to have the 
bank based in amsterdam or to have former dutch finance minister 
onno rudding picked as president 
in paris last month attali was elected 328 over rudding the 
banks two institutional members the european commission and the 
european investment bank abstained 
london received 23 votes as the venue for the banks 
headquarters while amsterdam and copenhagen got five votes each 
the dutch kept their finance minister at home tuesday and sent a 
lowlevel delegation to the signing ceremony instead 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

