<TEXT>
treasury secretary nicholas brady said tuesday 
that debtstrapped third world countries must reform their 
economies quickly to compete with emerging eastern european 
democracies for investors 
the incentive for the developing countries to move ahead 
vigorously with reform efforts has taken on additional urgency 
since the emergence of eastern europe brady said 
in the aggressive worldwide competition for foreign 
investment countries which fail to create an attractive investment 
environment run a real risk of lost opportunities and falling 
behind he said 
brady said the competition was for not only investment capital 
put up by commercial banks and other private interests but also for 
support from governments such as the united states 
we are committed to providing maximum possible support for 
marketoriented reforms in both regions of eastern europe and 
latin america brady said but lets face it the world is 
short of capital and governments are shorter still 
brady said the bush administration was channeling its aid both 
on a countrybycountry basis and through multinational lending 
organizations such as the world bank and the international monetary 
fund 
bradys remarks were made in a speech to the american chamber of 
commerce in london a text of the comments was released in 
washington 
brady praised the progress made under his 15monthold debt 
initiative in which commercial banks are provided incentives to 
forgive a portion of the 13 trillion debt being carried by third 
world countries 
so far six nations mexico venezuela costa rica morocco 
the philippines and chile have reached debtreduction agreements 
using guidelines of the brady plan 
brady said the commercial bank debt of the six nations accounts 
for nearly half the debt of the 16 largest debtor countries and 
that negotiations are underway to reach debt agreements with 
several other countries 
the crumbling of communist domination in eastern europe has 
grabbed the headlines but brady said revolutionary change has also 
been underway in latin america 
democratic elections in many latin american nations have 
produced a new generation of leaders committed to marketbased 
economic reforms he said brady addressed business leaders in 
london before traveling to paris for a ceremony establishing the 
new european bank for reconstruction and development aimed at 
providing assistance for eastern europe 
he also was leading the us delegation to the annual meeting of 
the 24nation organization of economic cooperation and development 
