william jovanovich joined harcourt brace amp co as a book 
salesman and editor in 1947 and built it into one of the nations 
leading publishers of textbooks as well a premier medical and 
professional publisher 
when he became president and chief executive in 1954 the 
company had annual sales of 8 million and employed 125 people 
last year it posted revenue of 13 billion and employed 6000 
people 
