and realize the full value of their respective assets 
the filing allows all of drexels operations to reorganize under 
court protection a move that would have been difficult had only 
the parent been in bankruptcy proceedings it also freezes 
outstanding litigation against any of the subsidiaries 
federal guidelines generally prohibit investment firms that do 
business with the public from seeking bankruptcy protection but 
drexel officials said the firm was able to make the filing because 
it no longer had any client accounts 
a revived drexel would not be expected to deal with the public 
